%description:
Regression test for RSVP-TE refresh reduction (RFC 2961 Section 5.4), using the
shipped examples/mpls/testte_failure network (RSVPTE4) with its LSR1_rsvp.xml/
LSR1_fec.xml traffic configuration but an empty scenario (no link failure): a single
explicitly-routed tunnel LSR1->LSR2->LSR4->LSR5, with "refreshReduction" turned on
for every LSR and "refreshInterval" shortened to 0.3s so several refresh cycles fit
into a short sim-time-limit.

Asserted:
  1. after the LSP is established (RsvpTe::processPATH_NOTIFY's "Path successfully
     established" line, ingress-only), Srefresh messages appear on both the Path
     side (RsvpTe::sendPathSrefresh's "sending SREFRESH (PSB" line) and the Resv
     side (RsvpTe::sendResvSrefresh's "sending SREFRESH (RSB" line) -- refresh
     reduction is doing compression in both directions, not just one;
  2. in that same post-establishment window, full Path/Resv refreshes
     (refreshPath()'s "refresh path (PSB" / the PER-PHOP refreshResv(rsb, PHOP)
     overload's "refresh reservation (RSB ...) PHOP ..." line) do NOT reappear --
     the periodic full resends have actually stopped, not merely "also" produced
     alongside Srefresh. (The outer, per-cycle refreshResv(rsb) wrapper also logs
     a bare "refresh reservation (RSB ...)" line every cycle regardless of
     whether it ends up compressing every one of its phops -- that ambiguous line
     is deliberately NOT asserted on; only the inner, phop-specific "... PHOP ..."
     line unambiguously means a full Resv actually went out.)
  3. the session survives at least 3x refreshInterval without its soft state
     expiring (DELIVERED postrun check: host traffic keeps flowing over the LSP for
     the whole run, which is only possible if Srefresh is correctly treated as a
     full refresh -- RsvpTe.cc's stateLifetimeFactor default (3) times the jittered
     refresh cadence means an un-refreshed PSB/RSB would time out and tear the LSP
     down well before sim-time-limit).

Falsification: reverting the refreshReduction/Srefresh code (or leaving
"refreshReduction" at its default false) makes assertion 1 fail outright (no
"sending SREFRESH" line is ever produced) -- verified manually against the parent
commit before writing this test.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.testte_failure.RSVPTE4
sim-time-limit = 3s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-event-banners = false
**.LSR*.rsvp.cmdenv-log-level = info
**.cmdenv-log-level = off
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-#${runnumber}.sca"

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host3"

**.host3.numApps = 1
**.host3.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host3.app[0].localPort = 100

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host4.rt"
**.host5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host5.rt"

**.LSR1.classifier.config = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR1_fec.xml")
**.LSR1.rsvp.traffic = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR1_rsvp.xml")

**.LSR*.rsvp.helloInterval = 0.2s
**.LSR*.rsvp.helloTimeout = 0.5s
**.LSR*.rsvp.refreshInterval = 0.3s
**.LSR*.rsvp.refreshReduction = true

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR5.rt"
**.LSR6.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR6.rt"
**.LSR7.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR7.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

**.scenarioManager.script = xml("<scenario/>")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# slice test.out to only the part after the LSP is up, so the assertions below are
%# about steady-state refresh behavior, not the (necessarily full) initial signaling
%postrun-command: awk '/Path successfully established/{f=1} f' test.out > after_establish.out
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 1a. Srefresh compression kicks in on the Path side
%contains: after_establish.out
sending SREFRESH (PSB
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 1b. Srefresh compression kicks in on the Resv side
%contains: after_establish.out
sending SREFRESH (RSB
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 2a. full Path refreshes have stopped
%not-contains: after_establish.out
refresh path (PSB
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 2b. full (per-phop) Resv refreshes have stopped -- see the description for why
%# this checks the inner "... PHOP ..." line specifically, not the outer wrapper's
%# unconditional per-cycle line
%not-contains-regex: after_establish.out
refresh reservation \(RSB \d+\) PHOP
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# 3. the session survives (>= 3x refreshInterval, i.e. 0.9s, well inside the 3s
%# run) without its soft state expiring -- traffic keeps being delivered over the LSP
%postrun-command: grep "packetReceived:count" results/General-#0.sca | awk '$NF > 0 { print "DELIVERED", $0 }' > delivered.out
%contains: delivered.out
DELIVERED
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
